## What I Learned

> The best AI systems know when *not* to use AI.

Using an agent for deterministic tasks wastes tokens, adds latency, and introduces unpredictability. The right pattern is: **code what you can 
predict, use AI only for what you can't.**

This project also showed that multi-agent handoffs require careful state management — context doesn't automatically transfer. If you need an agent 
to act on upstream data, you have to be explicit and structured about what gets passed.

